==ᱵᱤᱵᱟ.ᱫᱽ==
᱑᱑ ᱚᱜᱚᱥᱴ ᱒᱐᱑᱗ ᱨᱮ [[ᱡᱷᱟᱨᱠᱷᱚᱸᱰ]] ᱥᱚᱨᱠᱟᱨ ᱦᱟᱸᱥᱫᱟ-ᱟᱜ ''[[ᱫᱤ ᱟᱫᱤᱵᱟᱥᱤ ᱣᱤᱞ ᱱᱚᱴ ᱰᱟᱱᱥ : ᱠᱟ.ᱦᱱᱤ ᱢᱟᱞᱟ]]'' ᱯᱚᱛᱚᱵ ᱮ ᱵᱮᱱ ᱞᱮᱫ ᱛᱟᱭᱟ ᱟᱨ ᱱᱩᱭ ᱫᱚ ᱪᱟ.ᱠᱨᱤ ᱠᱷᱟᱱ ᱠᱚ ᱩᱰᱩᱠ ᱜᱤᱰᱤ ᱞᱮᱫᱮᱭᱟ ᱾ ᱱᱩᱠᱩᱣᱟᱜ ᱢᱮᱱ ᱫᱚ ᱟ.ᱫᱤᱵᱟ.ᱥᱤ ᱞᱟᱠᱪᱟᱨ ᱟᱨ ᱥᱟᱱᱛᱟᱲ ᱛᱤᱨᱞᱟ. ᱠᱚ ᱵᱟ.ᱲᱤᱡ ᱰᱟᱦᱟᱨ ᱛᱮ ᱚᱞ ᱩᱨᱩᱢ ᱞᱮᱫ ᱠᱚᱣᱟ ᱾ ᱚᱱᱟ ᱛᱮ ᱥᱚᱨᱠᱟᱨ ᱟᱡᱟᱜ ᱯᱚᱛᱚᱵ ᱫᱚ ᱵᱮᱱ ᱞᱮᱫᱟᱭ ᱾<ref>Sudipta Datta, '[http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/hansda-sowvendra-shekharfighting-a-ban/article19525262.ece Who is Hansda Sowvendra Shekhar, fighting a ban]', ''The Hindu'' (19 August 2017).</ref> ᱢᱩᱲᱩᱛ ᱠᱚᱢᱯᱞᱮᱱ ᱫᱚ ᱩᱱ ᱚᱠᱛᱚ ᱨᱤᱱᱤᱡ [[ᱡᱷᱟᱨᱠᱷᱚᱸᱰ]] ᱨᱤᱱᱤᱡ ᱨᱳᱞᱤᱝ ᱯᱟᱨᱴᱤ [[ᱵᱷᱟᱨᱚᱛᱤᱭᱚ ᱡᱚᱱᱚᱛᱟ ᱯᱟᱨᱴᱤ]], ᱵᱤᱨᱳᱫᱜᱤ [[ᱡᱷᱟᱨᱠᱷᱚᱸᱰ ᱢᱩᱠᱛᱤ ᱢᱩᱨᱪᱷᱟ]] ᱟᱨ [[ᱡᱟᱢᱤᱭᱟ ᱢᱤᱞᱤᱭᱟ ᱤᱥᱞᱟᱢᱤᱭᱟ]] ᱯᱟᱦᱴᱟ ᱠᱷᱚᱱ ᱟᱜᱩ ᱞᱮᱱᱟ ᱾ <ref>Ziya Us Salam, '[http://www.frontline.in/the-nation/a-santhal-suppressed/article9873860.ece A Santhal Suppressed]', ''Frontline'' (13 October 2017).</ref> The government's actions were widely criticised.<ref>Sanjay Srivastava, '[https://www.hindustantimes.com/opinion/what-the-ban-on-the-adivasi-will-not-dance-tells-us-about-india-s-political-life/story-gPtXIRpKwDcwl0zTEgEdVN.html What the ban on The Adivasi Will Not Dance tells us about India’s political life]', ''Hindustan Times'' (14 August 2017).</ref><ref>Ruchir Joshi, '[http://www.thehindu.com/opinion/columns/the-reader-will-not-dance/article19482115.ece The reader will not dance]', ''The Hindu'' (13 August 2017).</ref><ref>'[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/ranchi/dubbed-porn-book-on-tribals-banned-in-jharkhand/articleshow/60041186.cms Dubbed 'porn', book on tribals banned in Jharkhand', ''The Times of India'' (13 August 2017).]</ref><ref>'[https://thewire.in/171820/jharkhand-book-ban-condemned/ Writers, Activists Condemn Banning of ‘The Adivasi Will Not Dance’ in Jharkhand]', ''The Wire'' (29 August 2017).</ref> The ban on ''[[The Adivasi Will Not Dance: Stories]]'' was removed in December 2017<ref>{{cite web |url=https://scroll.in/latest/861308/four-months-after-ban-jharkhand-finds-nothing-objectionable-in-hansda-shekhars-book-on-adivasis |title=Four months after ban, Jharkhand finds nothing objectionable in Hansda Shekhar’s book on Adivasis |work=Scroll |author=Scroll Staff |date=December 13, 2017 |accessdate=September 2, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/india/jharkhand-govt-finds-nothing-objectionable-in-santhal-writers-book-ban-could-be-lifted-sowvendra-shekhar-hansda-4981307/ |title=Jharkhand: Govt finds nothing objectionable in Santhal writer’s book, ban could be lifted |work=The Indian Express |author=Prashant Pandey |date=December 14, 2017 |accessdate=September 2, 2018}}</ref> and Shekhar's suspension was removed and he was reinstated into his job in 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://indianculturalforum.in/2018/08/17/suspension-on-writer-hansda-sowvendra-shekhar-revoked/ |title=Suspension on Writer Hansda Sowvendra Shekhar Revoked |work=Indian Cultural Forum |author=ICF Team |date=August 17, 2018 |accessdate=September 2, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/express-sunday-eye/playing-with-fire-5334097/ |title=Playing with Fire: Hansda Sowvendra Shekhar on his first children's book |work=The Indian Express |author=Paromita Chakrabarti |date=September 2, 2018 |accessdate=September 2, 2018}}</ref>

